    faqs: [
      { q: 'Do I need the same brand of replacement wire?', a: "No. Boundary wire is generic 1mm copper-clad aluminium with PVC insulation. Husqvarna's wire is slightly heavier than generic but electrically identical to the cheaper alternatives. Generic wire from Amazon or eBay is half the price and works perfectly." },
      { q: 'Can I splice with electrical tape?', a: "No. Electrical tape fails outdoors within 12 months — moisture gets under the tape and corrodes the copper. Always use gel-filled crimp connectors designed for outdoor use." },
      { q: 'How deep should the wire be buried?', a: '5cm minimum, 10cm ideal. Below 10cm the signal weakens and the mower may not reliably detect the boundary. Above 5cm, garden forks and aerators will hit it.' },
      { q: 'Do I need to factory-reset the mower after a wire repair?', a: 'No. The mower will detect the restored loop signal automatically and resume normal operation. Only reset if you see persistent errors after the repair confirms continuity.' },
      { q: 'What if my dock is fine but the wire is broken in two places?', a: "Halve-the-loop diagnostic — find one break, splice it, then if the dock still shows 'no signal', repeat. Two simultaneous breaks are common after winter — a frost-heaved area can damage the wire in multiple places." }
    ]
